 {"id":"bd-3pcw","title":"Task: Add property-based tests for extension runtime","description":"# Task: Add Property-Based Tests for Extension Runtime

## Objective

Use proptest to verify invariants hold for all inputs, catching edge cases not covered by fixtures.

## Background

Property-based testing generates random inputs and verifies properties hold. This catches edge cases that manual test cases miss.

## Properties to Test

### 1. Hostcall Never Panics

No matter what input, hostcalls should return Ok or Err, never panic.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #[test]
    fn hostcall_never_panics(
        hostcall_type in "(tool|exec|http|session|ui|events)",
        method in "[a-z]{1,20}",
        args in any::<serde_json::Value>(),
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();
        let request = HostcallRequest {
            hostcall_type,
            method,
            args,
        };

        // Should not panic
        let _ = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(request);
    }
}
```

### 2. Invalid Type Returns Error

Unknown hostcall types always return an error.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #[test]
    fn invalid_type_returns_error(
        invalid_type in "[a-z]{1,20}".prop_filter("known types", |s| {
            \!["tool", "exec", "http", "session", "ui", "events"].contains(&s.as_str())
        }),
        method in "[a-z]{1,20}",
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();
        let request = HostcallRequest {
            hostcall_type: invalid_type,
            method,
            args: json\!({}),
        };

        let result = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(request);
        prop_assert\!(result.is_err());
    }
}
```

### 3. Missing Required Fields Return Error

Hostcalls with missing required fields return appropriate errors.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #[test]
    fn tool_register_requires_name(
        description in "[a-z ]{0,100}",
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();
        let request = HostcallRequest {
            hostcall_type: "tool".into(),
            method: "register".into(),
            args: json\!({
                "description": description,
                // name is missing
            }),
        };

        let result = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(request);
        prop_assert\!(result.is_err());
    }
}
```

### 4. State Consistency

Multiple operations don't corrupt state.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #[test]
    fn repeated_operations_consistent(
        ops in prop::collection::vec(any::<HostcallOp>(), 1..20),
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();

        for op in ops {
            let _ = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(op.to_request());
        }

        // Runtime should still be usable
        let status = runtime.health_check();
        prop_assert\!(status.is_ok());
    }
}
```

### 5. Unicode Handling

Unicode strings don't cause issues.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #[test]
    fn unicode_strings_handled(
        message in ".*",  // Any unicode string
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();

        // Show spinner with unicode
        let result = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(HostcallRequest {
            hostcall_type: "ui".into(),
            method: "showSpinner".into(),
            args: json\!({ "message": message }),
        });

        // Should succeed or return recoverable error
        if let Ok(response) = result {
            prop_assert\!(response.get("id").is_some());
        }
    }
}
```

### 6. Large Payloads

Large inputs don't cause memory issues.

```rust
proptest\! {
    #\![proptest_config(ProptestConfig::with_cases(10))]
    #[test]
    fn large_payload_handled(
        size in 1000..100_000usize,
    ) {
        let runtime = create_test_runtime_sync();
        let large_string = "x".repeat(size);

        let result = runtime.dispatch_hostcall_sync(HostcallRequest {
            hostcall_type: "ui".into(),
            method: "showNotification".into(),
            args: json\!({ "message": large_string }),
        });

        // Should not crash or hang
        prop_assert\!(result.is_ok() || result.is_err());
    }
}
```

